Meet <b>Kami</b>, our Citizen of the Week!<br><br>This laid-back chick has lived at 37814 Broadway Boulevard in Lakeview since May 16, 2005. In her almost two years as a Millsberry citizen, she has made tons of friends and accomplished a lot, seemingly effortlessly! People can't figure out how she has time for school, sports, fun, and friends, because she seems to do it all. <br><br>As an avid skateboarder and soccer player, she knows most of the sporty types around town. She likes to hang out at <a href="http://www.millsberry.com/peabody_park/">Peabody Park</a> after school, challenging people to beat her <a href="http://www.millsberry.com/gamepages/flashgame_ctp.phtml?game_id=360">Slap Shot Shootout</a> score. She's a totally adventurous girl, yet always remembers to wear proper safety gear&mdash;definitely a must with her attitude!<br><br>She's also known for being a serious music lover, and always knows the latest heavy metal and punk buzz bands. She has been getting into rap recently, and likes to hit up the <a href="http://www.millsberry.com/studio/">Millsberry Recording Studio</a> to create her own beats! <br><br>This everywhere girl is definitely someone to get to know. Maybe you'll discover how she does so much and always keeps her cool. Thanks for being a good citizen, Kami, and congratulations on being named Citizen of the Week!</div>
